1. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with first-order logic and introduces a new notion of blocked clauses in this context. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses a novel first-order preprocessing tool that can improve the performance of theorem provers. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper presents a polynomial algorithm for checking whether a clause is blocked. 
4. cs.PL (Programming Languages) is another possible category as the paper deals with a syntactic criterion for defining blocked clauses. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses a tool for preprocessing first-order problems.
